messages.title: WHO CAN CHALLENGE THE TORIES IN CHIPPING BARNET?
messages.content: Many voters have asked which Party can best challenge the Conservatives in Chipping Barnet. Labour have come second in all recent General Elections and nearly won in 1997 and 2001.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Labour has led the world in tackling the banking crisis and pulling the country out of recession. We will bring the deficit down without damaging the recovery and we will protect front line services.

mentions.tacticalSituation: Only voting Labour can challenge the Tories in this seat.

issues.economy: Labour has led the world in tackling the banking crisis and pulling the country out of recession. We will bring the deficit down without damaging the recovery and we will protect front line services.
